@startuml fig-modulation
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12

title Modulation Techniques: ASK, FSK, PSK and QAM

rectangle "Digital Data\n(baseband bit stream)" as data #FFF9C4
rectangle "Carrier Wave\n(sinusoidal at frequency f)" as carrier #E3F2FD

rectangle "ASK\nAmplitude Shift Keying\nVaries amplitude\nSimple but noise-sensitive" as ask #BBDEFB
rectangle "FSK\nFrequency Shift Keying\nVaries frequency\nMore robust than ASK" as fsk #BBDEFB
rectangle "PSK\nPhase Shift Keying\nVaries phase\nGood spectral efficiency" as psk #BBDEFB
rectangle "QAM\nQuadrature Amplitude Modulation\nVaries amplitude + phase\nHigh throughput (Wi-Fi, LTE)" as qam #E1BEE7

data -down-> ask
data -down-> fsk
data -down-> psk
data -down-> qam

carrier -down-> ask
carrier -down-> fsk
carrier -down-> psk
carrier -down-> qam

legend bottom
  Modulation impresses digital data onto
  an analogue carrier for transmission.
  QAM combines amplitude and phase variation
  to achieve higher data rates per symbol.
endlegend
@enduml
